feat: Add advanced search functionality for movies
- Implemented an advanced search endpoint in `MovieControllers` with support for filters: - Title - Genre - Minimum Rating - Release Date Range - Refactored `Movie` model: - Increased `genre` column length to 255. - Made `rating` column `nullable = false` to ensure consistency. - Updated `MovieRepository`: - Added a custom query `advancedSearch` for dynamic filtering of movies. - Removed unused methods (`findByTitle`, `findByGenre`, `findByRatingGreaterThanEqual`). - Enabled SQL logging in `application.properties` for better debugging. - Added comments for optional logging functionality in controllers.

feat: Add advanced search functionality for movies
- Implemented an advanced search endpoint in `MovieControllers` with support for filters: - Title - Genre - Minimum Rating - Release Date Range - Refactored `Movie` model: - Increased `genre` column length to 255. - Made `rating` column `nullable = false` to ensure consistency. - Updated `MovieRepository`: - Added a custom query `advancedSearch` for dynamic filtering of movies. - Removed unused methods (`findByTitle`, `findByGenre`, `findByRatingGreaterThanEqual`). - Enabled SQL logging in `application.properties` for better debugging. - Added comments for optional logging functionality in controllers.

refactor: Remove "not recommended" warning by replacing `@Autowired` with constructor injection
- Removed the `@Autowired` annotation in `MovieControllers`. - Replaced field injection with constructor injection for better Spring best practices. - Eliminated warnings regarding the use of `@Autowired` on fields.

feat: Add MovieSeeder for seeding initial movie data
- Implemented `MovieSeeder.java` to seed initial movie data into the database on application startup. - Added `@PrePersist` and `@PreUpdate` methods in `Movie.java` to set timestamps for `createdAt` and `updatedAt` fields. - The seeder includes sample movie entries such as "The Dark Knight", "Inception", and "The Matrix". - The `onCreate` and `onUpdate` methods ensure proper timestamp handling during persistence.

feat: Implement CRUD functionality for Movies
- Added `MovieControllers.java` to handle HTTP requests for CRUD operations. - Created `Movie.java` model to represent movie data schema. - Developed `MovieRepository.java` to interact with the database using Spring Data JPA. - Updated `application.properties` with necessary configurations.
